This paper focuses on creating a corpus of sarcasm in dialogue using natural language processing techniques, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of supervised learning and linguistic pattern learning, which are common techniques in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of lexico-syntactic cues, which is a subfield of information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language processing. The paper also discusses the qualitative analysis of linguistic differences, which falls under the category of computational social science (cs.SI) and cybernetics (cs.CY).
